fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.activation

Interface IRankedService<S>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - service type, normally an interface.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<IRankedService<S>>

    public interface IRankedService<S>
extends Comparable<IRankedService<S>>
    Sortable reference to a service implementation (referent). This provides access to declared subscriptions where the optional attribute is set to true.

    Sorting is primarily based on the service ranking. Secondary sorting may performed, if required, when the referent implements IAttachable and defines a version; the highest version will have the highest priority.

    Thread safety: implementations of this type are required to be immutable. This requirement does not apply to the referent accessible via this reference.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IServiceContext.getRankedServices(IService), PluginService, SystemService
